<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1884-04-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1884-04-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="372" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d372">
                        <head>No. 372.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Valera</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Frelinghuysen</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Spain</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1884-04-12"><hi rend="italic">April</hi> 12,
                                1884</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Highly esteemed Sir and Dear Friend</hi>: I tender
                            to you my sin-merest thanks for the prompt and effective orders you gave
                            for the protection of the Spanish consul at Key West, and also for the
                            reassuring news you sent me in your letter of yesterday.</p>
                        <p>Believe me, &amp;c.,</p>
                        <closer><signed>JUAN VALERA.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>